  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "High-level function calls first check that the called address has code by using `extcodesize`. This works around a peculiar detail of the EVM: Calls to contracts without code succeed silently instead of failing. For low-level calls (members of ``address``), this check is not present and that fact should be documented there.",
